  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Water Wells in the Horn of Africa (2015)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDPs, Poor families, Students</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing the one of the basic human needs is access to clean water. Today in the Horn of Africa, millions of people are suffering from diseases and death because there is a lack of access to clean water. Shallow, hand-dug water wells are inexpensive to build and can provide clean drinking water to thousands of villagers and their livestock for a dozen years or more. They also provide employment opportunities for local laborers and maintenance technicians as well as spare women and children from the difficult and dangerous work of fetching water from unsafe sources.</narrative>
  </description>
